When I first saw the petition, I thought to myself, why do druids need better heals?  Or rather, how can they ask for better heals when it is not their specialty?  I attempted to be very scientific, and look at the matter from all angles, and I finally realized something.  <br>
<br>
My main character is a wizard, and I also play a cleric.  Granted, neither have reached the end-game (because I'm a lazy piece of shit), so I don't speak from experience.  However, I do know a bit about the game, having played for about a year and a half.  From a cleric's perspective, I was thinking, &quot;DRUIDS CANNOT GET A BETTER HEAL, THAT WOULD BE STEPPING ON MY TOES!  WHAT WOULD I DO?&quot;  Then I thought, well... this would only affect them in raid situations.  It seems that everyone agrees that druids do not have a problem keeping a single exp group healed.  They are asking for a healing upgrade to help them in the end-game encounters.<br>
<br>
